Fixed up "Duplicates" link as this is no longer considered a duplicate as the test will also be modified.

Very unclear which bug to link CI test failures to.
[~coleenp] since you took on this bug, would you like to also look at JDK-8298991 which is a superset? (the same problem seems to exist in other vmTestbase/nsk/sysdict tests).
Fair enough, setting back to 'runtime'. Please keep in mind that JDK-8298991 might address the same issue, to avoid work duplication.
I still don't know why it only runs out of memory with ZGC.
We need to fix this test then. Help [~mseledtsov] !
We should probably fix the test to have more memory or handle OOM better. I'm going to open and send it back to runtime. Oh fun.
Closing this one as a duplicate of JDK-8298991, since the underlying cause of all failures appears to be the same (test runs out of memory).
Test also fails with "failed reallocation of scalar objects" like JDK-8298991.

These last two results have:
java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: Java heap space: failed reallocation of scalar replaced objects
And these are all ZGC. I think ZGC should have a look first.

Caused by: java.lang.ExceptionInInitializerError: Exception java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: Java heap space [in thread "nsk.sysdict.share.SysDictTest$Worker@1ad8f342"]

Looks like a simple OOM situation when running the test.
